# GitHub Linguist overrides.
#
# The Rust runtime kernel lives in the separate secure-exec repo; this repo is
# the TypeScript client + protocol + registry plus a large test suite. The rules
# below stop the language bar from being dominated by tests, the website, and
# generated bundles, and mark the TypeScript client layer as non-detectable so
# the repository's reported language reflects the Rust runtime it ships.

# --- TypeScript: client/protocol layer, excluded from the language bar ---
*.ts                                            linguist-detectable=false
*.tsx                                           linguist-detectable=false
*.mts                                           linguist-detectable=false
*.cts                                           linguist-detectable=false

# --- Generated artifacts (codegen / bundles) ---
*.d.ts                                          linguist-generated
packages/playground/agent-os-worker.js          linguist-generated

# --- Vendored third-party code (Linguist auto-detects vendor/, listed for clarity) ---
**/vendor/**                                    linguist-vendored

# --- Documentation & marketing site (not application source) ---
website/**                                      linguist-documentation
examples/**                                     linguist-documentation

# --- Build / CI tooling scripts (not shipped product code) ---
scripts/**                                      linguist-vendored
**/scripts/*.mjs                                linguist-vendored

# --- Tests excluded from the language bar (real code, not product source) ---
**/tests/**                                     linguist-detectable=false
**/test/**                                      linguist-detectable=false
